text:
Dyer Ave., north from West 34th to 42nd (background) Streets. This thoroughfare, recently constructed in the center of the blocks between Ninth and Tenth Aves., is actually the entrance through to new Lincoln Tunnel. No. 2 is similar from West 35th Street; the Tunnel mouth being at the base of the incline.

February 10, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.
